Gex_raw<-input_test_mod1$layers["counts"]
##Take rowsum greater than 0 shows have been already done
total_counts<-colSums(Gex_raw)
#total_counts
hist(total_counts,breaks=100)
abline(v=2000,col="red")

pzero <- 1-colMeans(Gex_raw>0)
plot(total_counts,pzero)

Gex<-Gex_raw[rowSums(Gex_raw)>0,]
print(dim(Gex))
## [1] 14813 13953
sz<-colSums(Gex)
pz<-colMeans(Gex==0)
pd<-data.frame(sz=sz,pz=pz)
(plt<-ggplot(pd,aes(x=sz,y=pz))+geom_point()+theme_bw()+xlab("total UMI per droplet")+ylab("fraction of zeros per droplet")+scale_x_log10())
(plt2<-ggExtra::ggMarginal(plt,type="histogram",fill="white",bins=100))

#ggs("total_umi_vs_pzero_ercc.pdf",plot=plt2)
##  variance!=mean
m<-rowMeans(Gex); v<-apply(Gex,1,var)
summary(v/m)
##      Min.   1st Qu.    Median      Mean   3rd Qu.      Max. 
##     3.058    14.747    22.741   241.818    39.972 14413.925
plot(log(m),log(v),xlab="log(mean)",ylab="log(var)")
abline(0,1,col="blue",lwd=2) #poi
curve(x+log1p(exp(x)/100),from=-8,to=7,add=TRUE,lty=2,col="red",lwd=2) #nb

N<-median(colSums(Gex))
predict_zeros_binom<-function(x){(1-exp(x)/N)^N} #binomial
predict_zeros_poi<-function(x){exp(-exp(x))}
predict_zeros_nb<-function(x,phi=100){
  exp(-phi*log1p(exp(x-log(phi))))
}

pd<-data.frame(log_mean=log(m),frac_zero=rowMeans(Gex==0))
xlo<-min(pd$log_mean)
xhi<-max(pd$log_mean)

with(pd,plot(log_mean,frac_zero,xlab="log of mean expression",ylab="fraction of zero droplets",cex=1.5,main="CITE Seq"))
curve(predict_zeros_binom,from=xlo,to=xhi,col="blue",lwd=4,add=TRUE)
curve(predict_zeros_poi,from=xlo,to=xhi,col="green",lwd=3,lty=2,add=TRUE)
curve(predict_zeros_nb(x,phi=10),from=xlo,to=xhi,col="red",lwd=3,lty=3,add=TRUE)
legend("bottomleft",c("Multinomial","Poisson","Negative Binomial"),lty=c(1,2,3),lwd=c(4,3,3),col=c("blue","green","red"))
